---
// This component requires no props as it holds the core narrative of the project.
---

<section id="vision" class="bg-tierra-madre py-24 px-[5%] md:px-[10%] flex justify-center items-center relative faja-divider">
  <div class="max-w-5xl w-full flex flex-col md:flex-row items-stretch gap-8 md:gap-12 py-4">

    <div class="hidden md:block relative min-w-[14px] flex-shrink-0 select-none" aria-hidden="true">
      <div class="absolute inset-y-0 left-1.5 w-2.5 bg-padre-sol translate-y-2"></div>
      <div class="absolute inset-y-0 left-0 w-2.5 bg-sangre-viva"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="md:hidden flex h-[14px] w-32 relative mb-2 select-none" aria-hidden="true">
       <div class="absolute inset-x-0 top-1.5 h-2.5 bg-padre-sol translate-x-2"></div>
       <div class="absolute inset-x-0 top-0 h-2.5 bg-sangre-viva"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="flex flex-col justify-center">
      <h2 class="font-title text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-[56px] text-agua-pura uppercase tracking-wider mb-10 leading-[1.1]">
        Kabunga —<br/> 
        <span class="text-padre-sol text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-[40px]">For the Community, For the World</span>
      </h2>
      
      <div class="space-y-8 text-fibra-natural/90 font-body text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed tracking-wide">
        <p>
          Globalization and modernization bring noise, spreading disinformation and threatening to fade the millenary knowledge of the Kamëntsá people. <span class="text-sangre-viva font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-sm border-b-2 border-sangre-viva pb-1 ml-2">This project is our answer.</span>
        </p>
        
        <p>
          For 10 years, our family has shared sacred <span class="italic text-padre-sol font-semibold tracking-wider">Yagé</span> medicine in a humble, basic Tambo on our ancestral land. Now, it is time to expand this home into a fully realized Cultural Center. 
        </p>

        <p class="pl-6 border-l-2 border-sombra-selva text-gray-300">
          Unlike private projects, our doors will be completely open to the entire native community for workshops, traditional gastronomy, and ancestral events, while offering travelers from all over the world a safe, loving space to slow down, heal, and remember.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
